    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic>d</italic> is the piezoelectric coefficient, and 
 <italic>F</italic> is the pressure. There are many types of piezoelectric materials, such as piezoelectric ceramics, polyvinylidene fluoride (PVDF), quartz crystal, etc. However, quartz crystal has the advantages of stable piezoelectric performance, high mechanical strength, and high insulation impedance, and is commonly used as the sensitive unit of piezoelectric pressure sensor [
